'''Carlisle Public Schools''' is a [[school district]] in [[Carlisle, Massachusetts]], [[United States|USA]]. The superintendent is Joyce Mehaffey.{{Citation needed|date=June 2011}} As of 2006, the district employed 79 faculty members and served 790 students in [[educational stages|grades]] [[kindergarten|pre-K]]&ndash;[[eighth grade|8]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Sally |last=Heaney |title=School changes bring unrest |url=http://www.boston.com/news/local/articles/2006/09/17/school_changes_bring_unrest/ |work=[[The Boston Globe]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |date=17 September 2006 |accessdate=6 April 2009 |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5fp91H1hD |archivedate=2009-04-06 }}</ref>
The district manages an elementary school and middle school collectively known as Carlisle School. The principal of the elementary school is Patrice Hurley and the principal of the middle school is Joyce Mehaffey. The school was established in 1848 as a [[One-room school|one-room school house]].<ref>{{cite news |first=David |last=Flannery |title=Buildings and Facilities |url=http://www.carlisle.k12.ma.us/district/facilities/buildings.htm |publisher=Carlisle Public Schools |date=8 January 2002 |accessdate=6 April 2009 }}</ref>
